Birb TV Setup Guide

1. Create systemd service

sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/birbtv.service

2. Verify venv setup (optional but recommended)

ls venv/bin/
which python
/home/k/coding_projects/birb_tv/venv/bin/python --version

3. Add service configuration

[Unit]
Description=Birb TV Camera App
After=network.target

[Service]
User=k
WorkingDirectory=/home/k/coding_projects/birb_tv
ExecStart=/home/k/coding_projects/birb_tv/venv/bin/python /home/k/coding_projects/birb_tv/app.py
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

4. Save and exit

CTRL + X
Y
Enter

5. Enable and start the service

sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl enable birbtv
sudo systemctl start birbtv

6. Check service status

sudo systemctl status birbtv

7. Reboot test (important)

sudo reboot

8. Access the app

http://<PI_IP>:5000

9. View logs (if needed)

journalctl -u birbtv -f